Pre-Game Insights: Both teams are desperate to earn their first wins of the section.
We are expecting an attacking affair between Kyrgyzstan and North Korea on Tuesday night.
Kyrgyzstan have struggled to get going in the section so far, meaning that we can imagine the visitors edging to victory in Bishkek.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The White Falcons commenced their October international window with a heavy defeat at the home of the 2022 World Cup hosts Qatar, who eased past their stuttering visitors 3-1 courtesy of goals from Almoez Ali, Ibrahim Al-Hassan and an own goal from Tamirlan Kozubaev.

The North Korea's senior men are failing in their attempts to qualify for a first World Cup finals since South Africa in 2010, with Tuesday's visitors yet to earn a win from three matches in Group A of third-round qualifying.
Others: Kyrgyzstan possible starting lineup: Tokotaev; Mischenko, Zarypbekov, Kichin, Kenzhebaev; Abdurahmonov, Uzdenov, Shukurov; Uulu, Kojo
North Korea possible starting lineup: Ju-Hyok; Ok-Chol, Kum-Song, Yu-Song, Pom-Hyok; Chung-Song, Kuk-Chol, Kuk-Bom, Il-Song; Kwang-Song, Kuk-Jin
